Editorial Reviews

Amazon.com
Kicking off with a dead-on Carol Channing impersonation, the most popular openly gay male entertainer in America rumbles through 66 minutes of gags, half-growled songs ("Frankie and Johnny," "This Is Not Going to Be Pretty"), and tragi-comic monologues. The best example of the latter is "Pouf Positive," a 14-minute AIDS saga, alternately sad, poignant, and uproarious. --Jeff Bateman 

Product Description
The three-time Tony Award-winning actor and playwright(Torch Song Trilogy, La Cage Aux Folles, Independence Day, Mrs. Doubtfire, Bullets Over Broadway) releases a performance album that displays the multiple dimensions of his very special talent. Recorded live at New York&#039;s Bottom Line, this provocative album includes stand-up comedy, two compelling dramatic monologues, and Harvey&#039;s distinctive musical style. Hilarious, moving and completely entertaining, this album is destined to be a classic in the vein of Lenny Bruce and George Carlin.
